President Obama has announced a Presidential Delegation to attend the 20th Commemoration of the Rwandan Genocide on April 7, 2014. The delegation will be led by Samantha Power, the United States Ambassador to the United Nations. Other members of the delegation include United States Ambassador to Rwanda Donald W. Koran, Member of the United States House of Representatives Karen Bass, Assistant Secretary of State for African Affairs Linda Thomas-Greenfield, Ambassador-at-Large for Global Criminal Justice Stephen J. Rapp, Special Representative for the African Great Lakes Region and the Democratic Republic of the Congo Russell Feingold, Senior Fellow at the ONE Campaign and Washington Post columnist Michael Gerson, and former Program Coordinator for the United States Agency for International Development Christine Hjelt.